'''保羅·克列布尼科夫'''（[[英文|英文]]：'''Paul Klebnikov'''，{{bd|1963年|6月3日|2004年|7月9日|}}）是一名[[俄裔美国人|美籍俄裔]]的[[記者|記者]]和[[歷史學家|歷史學家]]。他曾在《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》雜誌工作超過10年，去世時職位是[[俄文|俄文]]版主編。他2004年在[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]遇害，此事件被視為[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]打擊新聞調查的一項動作。雖然嫌犯指向3名[[車臣人|車臣人]]，但最後遭無罪釋放，他們似乎是被僱用的殺手，直至2009年，謀殺案的組織者仍未確定<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/2009/07/07/russia-journalists-politics-who-killed-paul-klebnikov-heidi-brown.html |title=Who Killed Paul Klebnikov? |author=Brown, Heidi |date=2009-07-07 |work=Forbes |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BArbNa3r?url=http://www.forbes.com/2009/07/07/russia-journalists-politics-who-killed-paul-klebnikov-heidi-brown.html |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>。

==早期生活==
保羅·克列布尼科夫出生於[[美國|美國]][[紐約|紐約]]一個[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]流亡者的家庭，其家族擁有悠久的[[軍事|軍事]]與[[政治|政治]]傳統，他的曾曾曾祖父Ivan Pouschine在1825年參與了俄羅斯著名的[[十二月黨人起義|十二月黨人起義]]，因而被流放到[[西伯利亞|西伯利亞]]；他的曾祖父是[[白俄羅斯|白俄羅斯]]的[[海軍上將|海軍上將]]，後遭[[布尔什维克|布尔什维克]]暗殺而亡。

年幼時期的他被稱為冒失鬼，常做出一些危險的舉動，包括在[[颶風|颶風]]來襲時去海邊游泳<ref name=NYM>{{cite web |url=http://nymag.com/nymetro/news/people/features/10193/ |title=The Assassination of a Dream |author=Pohl, Otto |date=2005-05-21 |work=New York |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAsORVpN?url=http://nymag.com/nymetro/news/people/features/10193/ |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref><ref name=E>{{cite web |url=http://www.economist.com/node/2921517?story_id=2921517 |title=Paul Klebnikov |date=2004-07-15 |work=The Economist |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-04 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAqd6d7e?url=http://www.economist.com/node/2921517?story_id=2921517 |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>，後來進入聖伯納學院和[[菲利普斯埃克塞特學院|菲利普斯埃克塞特學院]]就讀<ref name=CBS>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/elements/2005/04/26/48hours/timeline691023.shtml |title=Klebnikov timeline |publisher=CBS News |accessdate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBfD0Q4W?url=http://www.cbsnews.com/elements/2005/04/26/48hours/timeline691023.shtml |archivedate=2012-10-05 }}</ref>，並於1984年畢業於[[柏克萊加州大學|柏克萊加州大學]]，並取得[[政治學|政治學]]學士學位<ref name=NYM/>。隨後為了鍛鍊自己，他進入[[美國|美國]][[海軍陸戰隊|海軍陸戰隊]]的候補軍官學校就讀，但完成學業後，他拒絕了學校所提供的獎學金<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/12/26/magazine/26KLEBNIKOV.html?ref=paulklebnikov&pagewanted=print&position=&_r=0 |title=Back to Russia, With Love |author=Landesman, Paul |date=2004-12-26 |work=The New York Times |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAx1qfx2?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/12/26/magazine/26KLEBNIKOV.html?ref=paulklebnikov |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>。

相反地，他前往[[倫敦政治經濟學院|倫敦政治經濟學院]]攻讀博士學位，並因為傑出的俄羅斯研究，在此贏得Leonard Schapiro Prize<ref name=CBS />；他的博士論文題目與[[彼得·阿尔卡季耶维奇·斯托雷平|彼得·阿尔卡季耶维奇·斯托雷平]]這位俄羅斯帝國內政大臣有關<ref name=E />；1987-1988年間，他曾在[[倫敦|倫敦]]的歐洲研究學會演講<ref name=CBS />。

1991年9月22日，他娶了Helen "Musa" Train為妻，其為[[華爾街|華爾街]]銀行家John Train的女兒<ref name=NYM/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/09/23/style/helen-train-wed-to-paul-klebnikov.html |title=Helen Train Wed to Paul Klebnikov |date=1991-09-23 |work=The New York Times |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBfY6w3z?url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/09/23/style/helen-train-wed-to-paul-klebnikov.html |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>，婚後育有3名子女<ref name=NYM/>。

==在俄羅斯的報導==
克列布尼科夫1989年加入[[美國|美國]]雜誌《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》旗下，後因揭露前[[蘇聯|蘇聯]]貪腐黑幕而聲名鵲起<ref name=E />；1996年，據傳他為《福布斯》撰寫了封面故事，標題為「克林姆宮的教父？（Godfather of the Kremlin?）」，以[[義大利|義大利]][[黑手黨|黑手黨]]暗喻俄國大亨[[鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基|鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基]]。該篇文章雖然未署名，不過外界普遍認為作者即是克列布尼科夫，他也收到了死亡威脅，於是他暫停報導工作，回到[[法國|法國]][[巴黎|巴黎]]與妻兒團聚<ref name=NYM/> 。

[[鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基|鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基]]隨後在[[英國|英國]]法院控告《福布斯》誹謗，相關當局在該事件的管轄權上幾番轉折後<ref>{{cite book|last1=Delta|first1=George B.|last2=Matsuura|first2=Jeffrey H.|title=Law of the Internet|accessdate=2013-10-31|edition=3rd|volume=1|year=2008|publisher=Aspen Publishers|isbn=0-7355-7559-2|pages=3-92|chapter=Jurisdictional issues in cyberspace|quote=Berezovsky is the leading case in what has come to be known as “libel tourism}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Crook|first=Tim|title=Comparative media law and ethics|accessdate=2013-10-31|year=2010|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=0-415-55161-7|pages=240-241|chapter=Defamation law}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Taylor|first=Daniel C.|date=November 2010|title=Libel Tourism: Protecting Authors and Preserving Comity|journal=Georgetown Law Journal|publisher=Georgetown University|volume=99|page=194|issn=0016-8092|url=http://georgetownlawjournal.org/files/pdf/99-1/Taylor.pdf|accessdate=2013-10-31|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102154742/http://georgetownlawjournal.org/files/pdf/99-1/Taylor.pdf|archivedate=2014-01-02}}</ref>；2003年，[[鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基|鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基]]勝訴，該文章部分內容被限縮<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.economist.com/node/1632864 |title=Shuddup |date=2003-03-13 |work=Forbes |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAsp73Dr?url=http://www.economist.com/node/1632864 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref><ref>The following statement appended to the article on the Forbes website summarizes: 'On March 6, 2003 the resolution of the case was announced in the High Court in London. FORBES stated in open court that (1) it was not the magazine's intention to state that Berezovsky was responsible for the murder of Listiev, only that he had been included in an inconclusive police investigation of the crime; (2) there is no evidence that Berezovsky was responsible for this or any other murder; (3) in light of the English court's ruling, it was wrong to characterize Berezovsky as a mafia boss. [http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/0331/022.html"Berezovsky Vs. Forbes"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/0331/022.html |date=20190515074543 }} Forbes March 31, 2003</ref>。

同時，克列布尼科夫將他2000年出版的著作《克林姆宮教父—鲍里斯·別列佐夫斯基在俄國的掠奪》加以擴編<ref name=E/><ref name="godfather">{{cite book | last =Klebnikov | first =Paul | title =Godfather of the Kremlin: Boris Berezovsky and the looting of Russia | publisher =Harcourt | year =2000 | page =400 | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=vb2ZAAAAIAAJ | id =ISBN 0-15-100621-0, ISBN 978-0-15-100621-2 | access-date =2013-10-31 | archive-date =2017-03-21 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20170321231358/https://books.google.com/books?id=vb2ZAAAAIAAJ | dead-url =no }} A 2001 edition is entitled ''Godfather of the Kremlin: The Decline of Russia in the Age of Gangster Capitalism''.</ref>，增加了採訪前[[俄國|俄國]]總統[[葉爾欽|葉爾欽]]保鑣頭子亞歷山大·柯爾札可夫（Aleksandr Korzhakov）的內容，主要描述[[葉爾欽|葉爾欽]]所進行的「私有化」過程其實是[[葉爾欽|葉爾欽]]的「掠奪本紀」，並詳盡介紹俄國商人各種貪汙行為，許多內容特別針對[[鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基|鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基]]<ref name=NYT>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/10/13/books/books-of-the-times-a-tycoon-s-meteoric-rise-after-russia-s-collapse.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=A Tycoon's Meteoric Rise After Russia's Collapse |author=Bernstein, Richard |date=2000-10-13 |work=The New York Times |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAvigb4E?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/10/13/books/books-of-the-times-a-tycoon-s-meteoric-rise-after-russia-s-collapse.html?pagewanted=all |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

這本書在[[新聞|新聞]]界的褒貶不一<ref name=NYM/>，一位《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》專欄作家稱讚此書「豐富詳盡」且「情感強烈」<ref name=NYT />；許多俄國記者則認為此書太過依賴前[[克格勃|克格勃]]官員的證詞，只具參考作用；還有一位俄國評論家形容它為「八卦的集合」<ref name=NYM/>。

克列布尼科夫2003年公布第二本著作《與野蠻人的對話：盜匪、伊斯蘭教和車臣指揮官》，這本書紀錄了一場漫長的訪談，受訪者是[[車臣|車臣]]反政府武裝領導人艾哈邁德（Khozh Noukhayev），受訪過程中，[[伊斯蘭|伊斯蘭]]和[[車臣|車臣]]社會皆表達了各自的看法<ref>{{cite web |url=http://travel.nytimes.com/2005/06/17/international/europe/17russia.html |title=Prosecutor Says Chechen Rebel Had Editor Killed |author=Myers, Steven Lee |date=2005-06-17 |work=The New York Times |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAwm8WD2?url=http://travel.nytimes.com/2005/06/17/international/europe/17russia.html?_r=0 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

同年，克列布尼科夫成為[[俄文|俄文]]版《福布斯》的首位主編，由於他的妻兒並沒有前往[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]居住的意願，因此他答應只擔任該職位1年<ref name=NYM/>。該雜誌在他死前只討論了4個議題，其中一篇文章主題與俄國100名富豪有關，一些評論家推測這可能是他遇害的原因<ref name=NYM/>。

==謀殺==
2004年7月9日深夜，克列布尼科夫從《福布斯》辦公室離開後，在[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]街頭遭人開槍射擊<ref name=NYM />；遭槍擊後仍有意識，但由於將他送往急救的[[救護車|救護車]]上未攜帶氧氣瓶，最後在醫院通往手術房的電梯裡過世<ref name=NYT2>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/07/18/world/editor-s-death-raises-questions-about-change-in-russia.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=Editor's Death Raises Questions About Change in Russia |author=Chivers, C.J.; Arvedlund, Erin E.; Kishkovsky, Sophia |date=2004-07-18 |work=The New York Times |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAyHy5po?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/07/18/world/editor-s-death-raises-questions-about-change-in-russia.html?pagewanted=all |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

當局指此事件為買兇殺人<ref name=NYT2 />；[[俄文|俄文]]版《福布斯》的出版商則指此事件與克列布尼科夫的報導「絕對有關」<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/frontlineworld/rough/2007/05/russia_putin_vsint.html |title=The Last Independent Newspaper in Russia |author=Poolos, Alexandra |work=FrontLine |publisher=PBS |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAyWUc5D?url=http://www.pbs.org/frontlineworld/rough/2007/05/russia_putin_vsint.html |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>；各家評論則指克列布尼科夫之前撰寫的俄國百名富豪相關文章，恐怕就是引來殺機的原因，有人甚至懷疑背後主使者就是[[鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基|鲍里斯·阿布拉莫维奇·别列佐夫斯基]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ajr.org/article.asp?id=4287 |title=Iron Curtain Redux |author=Riccardi, Sherry |date=February/March 2007 |work=American Journalism Review |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BAyhbhrM?url=http://www.ajr.org/article.asp?id=4287 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/richardbehar/2013/03/24/did-boris-berezovsky-kill-himself-more-compelling-did-he-kill-forbes-editor-paul-klebnikov/ |title=Did Boris Berezovsky Kill Himself? More Compelling, Did He Kill Forbes Editor Paul Klebnikov |first=Richard |last=Behar |work=Forbes |date=2013-03-24 |accessdate=2013-10-31 |archive-date=2013-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523104111/http://www.forbes.com/sites/richardbehar/2013/03/24/did-boris-berezovsky-kill-himself-more-compelling-did-he-kill-forbes-editor-paul-klebnikov/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
==俄方的調查==
2006年，俄國檢方指控[[車臣|車臣]]反政府武裝領導人艾哈邁德為幕後策劃者，3名[[車臣人|車臣人]]被逮捕，分別是杜庫佐夫（Kazbek Dukuzov）、烏克耶夫（Musa Vakhayev）和桑德烈紀諾夫（Fail Sadretdinov），他們被以謀殺罪名起訴，但被判無罪。後來桑德烈紀諾夫因犯下其他罪行而被判9年監禁；杜庫佐夫、烏克耶夫2人的無罪判決則被[[俄國|俄國]]最高法院駁回，但兩人仍可上訴<ref name=NYT3>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/16/world/europe/16klebnikov.html?_r=2& |title=2 Suspects Absent in Moscow in Retrial Over Editor’s Killing |author=Myers, Steven Lee |date=1990-02-16 |work=The New York Times |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBhCxN1N?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/16/world/europe/16klebnikov.html?_r=3 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

2007年7月，此事件3週年時，[[美國國務院|美國國務院]]公開抗議俄國政府未能將犯人逮捕歸案，要求進一步調查<ref>{{cite web |url=http://2001-2009.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2007/87836.htm |title=Russia: Anniversary of Klebnikov Murder |author=McCormack, Sean |date=2007-07-08 |publisher=US Department of State |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBiRXgmO?url=http://2001-2009.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2007/87836.htm |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>，當時的[[美國總統|美國總統]][[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]也直接向俄國總理[[普京|普京]]提出要求<ref name=halt>{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/17/us-russia-klebnikov-idUSL1714098320071217 |title=Russia halts retrial over murdered U.S. reporter |author=Solovyov, Dmitry |agency=Reuters |date=2007-12-17 |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBhql7RR?url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/17/us-russia-klebnikov-idUSL1714098320071217 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

該案於2007年重啟調查，但仍未能確認嫌犯之犯行<ref name=NYT3/>；12月17日，因為杜庫佐夫未能配合調查，該案再遭推遲<ref name=halt/>，整起案件進入停滯期<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/12/world/europe/12klebnikov.html?pagewanted=all |title=Murder Highlights Russian System’s Flaws |author=Barry, Ellen |date=2009-07-11 |work=The New York Times |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBi721Au?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/12/world/europe/12klebnikov.html?_r=1 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

2009年7月，俄方再度啟動調查，並宣稱不再認定[[車臣|車臣]]反政府武裝領導人艾哈邁德為幕後策劃者，但仍認為他有參與該槍擊事件<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/2009/07/10/new-klebnikov-investigation-opinions-summit.html |title=Russia To Work With U.S. On New Klebnikov Inquiry |author=Brown, Heidi |date=2009-07-10 |work=Forbes |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBj67QUj?url=http://www.forbes.com/2009/07/10/new-klebnikov-investigation-opinions-summit.html |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

==榮譽==
2004年，國際組織[[保護記者協會|保護記者協會]]（Committee to Protect Journalists）追授保羅·克列布尼科夫為[[國際新聞自由獎|國際新聞自由獎]]的4位得主之一<ref name="2004 awards">{{cite web |url=http://cpj.org/awards/2004/ |title=International Press Freedom Awards 2004 |publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69pUS7T3k?url=http://cpj.org/awards/2004/ |archivedate=2012-08-11 |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

以克列布尼科夫命名的「保羅·克列布尼科夫」基金會成立，該基金會每年頒發勇氣獎給優秀記者，並提供機會給俄裔年輕記者到西方媒體企業實習<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rferl.org/content/article/1062275.html |title=Fund Gives Russian Editor First 'Courage' Prize |date=2005-10-20 |publisher=Radio Free Europe |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-10-05 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBjnkYYr?url=http://www.rferl.org/content/article/1062275.html |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.paulklebnikovfund.org/about-fund.htm |title=About the Fund |publisher=Paul Klebnikov Fund |archivedate=2012-10-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6BBjs1Pds?url=http://www.paulklebnikovfund.org/about-fund.htm |accessdate=2013-10-31 }}</ref>。

他在[[菲利普斯埃克塞特學院|菲利普斯埃克塞特學院]]時期的同學們創立了克列布尼科夫講座來緬懷他，第一屆講座在2006年5月12日舉行，這天同時也是他們的25年同學會，當天由《[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]]》記者、同時也是埃克塞特校友Jon Karp發表演說。
<ref>{{cite web |url=http://phillips.exeter.edu/pdfs/karp_klebnikov_assembly.pdf |title=Travels and Truth: In memory of Paul Klebnikov |accessdate=2013-10-31 |last=Jonathan |first=Karp |date=2006-05-12 |format=PDF |publisher=[[Phillips_Exeter_Academy|Phillips Exeter Academy]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070703113345/http://phillips.exeter.edu/pdfs/karp_klebnikov_assembly.pdf |archivedate=2007-07-03 }}</ref>
===克列布尼科夫計畫===
克列布尼科夫計畫是一個全球性的聯盟，專門針對克列布尼科夫謀殺案發布新訊息或推動調查工作，此計畫成立於2005年7月<ref>{{cite news | title = US Journalists Investigate Klebnikov Murder | work = The Moscow Times | date = 2005-07-15 | url = http://www.themoscowtimes.com/news/article/us-journalists-investigate-klebnikov-murder/221889.html | accessdate = 2013-10-31 | archive-date = 2015-12-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151226195205/http://www.themoscowtimes.com/news/article/us-journalists-investigate-klebnikov-murder/221889.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>，成員包括20名以上的記者和合作的媒體公司<ref name="mainvilletorontostar">{{cite news | last =Mainville | first =Michael | title =Questions remain in murder of U.S. editor - Moscow Calls for an open trial denied as Chechens are secretly tried as assassins, writes Michael Mainville Moscow | work =[[The_Toronto_Star|The Toronto Star]] | page =A15 | publisher =Toronto Star Newspapers Limited | date =2006-01-29 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Brown | first = Heidi | coauthors = Andrew Gillies | title = Back To Square One | work = [[Forbes_(magazine)|Forbes]] | publisher = Forbes.com LLC | date = 2006-05-05 | url = http://www.forbes.com/2006/05/05/klebnikov-verdict-innocent-cz_hb_0505klebnikov_2.html | accessdate = 2013-10-31 | archive-date = 2012-10-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121023100836/http://www.forbes.com/2006/05/05/klebnikov-verdict-innocent-cz_hb_0505klebnikov_2.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>，這些記者分別來自國際上知名媒體或新聞相關機構<ref>{{cite news | last = CBS News | title = The Man Who Knew Too Much: ''48 Hours Mystery'' Reports On Murder Of U.S. Journalist In Moscow | work = 48 Hours Mystery | publisher = CBS | date = 2006-07-01 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2005/04/28/48hours/main691763_page12.shtml | accessdate = 2008-07-14 | archive-date = 2013-11-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131102183203/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2005/04/28/48hours/main691763_page12.shtml | dead-url = no }}</ref>，包括《[[浮華世界|浮華世界]]》、[[CBS|CBS]]的著名節目「60分鐘」、[[紐約大學|紐約大學]]新聞系、《[[經濟學人|經濟學人]]》、[[彭博社|彭博社]]和《福布斯》等等<ref name="gershman">{{cite news | last =Gershman | title =Unusual U.S.-Russian Reporting Team To Probe Editor's Murder in Moscow | work =The New York Sun | date =2005-09-15 }}</ref><ref name="franchetti">{{cite news | last = Franchetti | first = Mark | title = Journalists turn detective to seek murderers of Moscow editor | work = [[The_Sunday_Times|The Sunday Times]] | pages = 26 | date = 2005-07-24}}</ref>。發起人為8位分別來自[[彭博社|彭博社]]、《[[浮華世界|浮華世界]]》和《福布斯》的記者，在2005年7月9日、也就是克列布尼科夫遇害一年後啟動了此計畫。記者理查·貝哈（Richard Behar）為該組織的董事<ref>{{cite news | last = Goodman | first = Amy | title = Anna Politkovskaya, Prominent Russian Journalist, Putin Critic and Human Rights Activist, Murdered in Moscow | work = Democracy Now! | date = 2006-10-09 | url = http://www.democracynow.org/2006/10/9/anna_politkovskaya_prominent_russian_journalist_putin | accessdate = 2008-07-14 | archive-date = 2019-12-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191218161604/https://www.democracynow.org/2006/10/9/anna_politkovskaya_prominent_russian_journalist_putin | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

